      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the butternut squash is fork-tender, roughly mash it with a fork</p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>,<strong> </strong>then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan along with the <strong>mashed butternut squash</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min until all the spinach has wilted and the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>butternut squash dal</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
